post_text:
Akron Prep is proud to be apart of the community that we have been privileged to serve in. We are not only here to educate all the students of this great community, we are here to stand in solidarity as we fight against social, racial and economic injustice.

The racial injustices of the past few weeks have made it even more clear that we are still living through not just Covid-19, but through a ‚Äúracial pandemic‚Äù as well.

This racial pandemic has continued on for centuries and has shown little to no signs of diminution . The recent superfluous killings of George Floyd, Ahmaud Arbery, and Breonna Taylor, among others, were not only disturbing , they were inhumane‚Ä¶

Akron Prep is committed to engaging in the fight against injustices, by teaching and leading the next generation.We are further committed to ongoing conversations with the community leaders about how we can make Akron Prep a safe place for our staff, scholars and families.

We will rise out of the ashes like a Phoenix!

Lion Strong!
Akron Strong!

Principal Ashley Miles
Akron Preparatory School

post_text:
As a reminder, there is no school tomorrow, Monday, March 16th through April 3rd.

If your child has medication left at school, parents can pick them up tomorrow (Monday) between 10:00am and 1:00pm.

We also will be serving two meals tomorrow between 10:00am-1:00pm. This is a grab and go service we will be providing throughout the duration of the break Mon-Fri.

Lastly, if your child was absent on Friday and didn't take home work, they can pick up between 10:00-1:00pm.

Please check out our fb post daily for updates .
